Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. In large bowl, combine ricotta cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese; set aside. In another bowl, thoroughly combine pasta and Pasta Sauce. In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spoon 1/2 of the pasta mixture; evenly top with cheese mixture, then remaining pasta mixture. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through. Serve, if desired, with additional heated Sauce.